The `drift config theme NAME` command sets the user's theme preference by writing the theme name to .drift/user-settings.xml (not committed to git). `drift config theme` with no name prints the current effective theme. The theme name must be one of the 12 built-in themes (see <ref spec="output.built_in_themes">built-in themes</ref>); unknown names are rejected with an error listing available themes. The setting is per-user and per-project — two developers on the same project can have different themes. This preference is overridden by .drift/theme.xml (project-level, committed) per the <ref spec="output.custom_theme">theme resolution precedence</ref>. See <ref spec="output_impl.user_settings">user settings</ref>.